    "abstract": "<jats:p>COVID-19 pandemic has spawned the need for mass production of N-95 respirators. We used Sterilization Wraps to produce face masks which maintained 93% particle capture efficacy post sterilization. This ubiquitously available material could be explored for production of high quality face masks at a cost less than 30 US cents.</jats:p>",
